Recommendations:
We recommended and the management agreed of the following:
Direct the Office of the Municipal Accountant to conduct a thorough analysis of the receivable accounts to include determination whether the claims were already impaired, or not and to set up the corresponding allowance for impairment, if any;
For dormant receivable accounts, follow the procedures and guidelines prescribed in COA Circular No. 2023-008 on its proper disposition/write-off with consideration of the effectivity which is for a period of one year;
Record the necessary adjusting and/or correcting entries if circumstances warrant as a result of the thorough analysis; and
The concerned office to review of the existing Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) of the loans granted to individual and establish a policy to enforce collectability if not provided therein.

Recommendations:
We recommended and the management agreed of the following:
The Management require all officials and employees to liquidate their cash advances immediately and institute appropriate legal sanction against concerned officials or employees, by withholding or suspension of their salaries;
The Office of the Municipal Accountant send a confirmation letter to the COA-ICFAU to ascertain whether the liquidation reports of the prior years’ intelligence fund submitted by their office have been duly received by the COA-ICFAU, in order to immediately liquidate said cash advance in the books, if these reports were in fact submitted;
The Office of the Municipal Accountant to retrieve and reconcile all available records pertaining to the cash advances granted from the prior years’, especially to those with no names and other relevant information indicated on its aging of cash advances; and
For dormant unliquidated cash advances as thoroughly determined by the Office of the Municipal Accountant, follow the procedures and guidelines prescribed in COA Circular No. 2023-008 on its proper disposition/write-off with consideration of the effectivity which is for a period of one year.

